SIMPLE: guzzle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guzzle
<hw>Guz"zle</hw> <pr>(g⟦ucr⟧z"z'l)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Guzzled</conjf>
<pr>(g⟦ucr⟧z"z'ld)</pr>, <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Guzzling</conjf> <pr>(g⟦ucr⟧z"zl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[OP. <ets>gosillier</ets>, prob. orig., to pass through the throat;
akin to F. <ets>gosier</ets> throat; cf. It. <ets>gozzo</ets> a bird's
crop.]</ety> <def>To swallow liquor greedily; to drink much or
frequently.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those that came to <qex>guzzle</qex> in his wine cellar.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Well-seasoned bowls the gossip's spirits raise,⟦br⟧
Who, while she <qex>guzzles</qex>, chats the doctor's praise.</q>
<rj><qau>Roscommon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To fat the <qex>guzzling</qex> hogs with floods of whey.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guzzle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Guzzle
<hw>Guz"zle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To swallow much or often; to
swallow with immoderate gust; to drink greedily or continually; <as>as,
one who <ex>guzzles</ex> beer</as>.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guzzle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Guzzle
<hw>Guz"zle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An insatiable thing or
person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That sink of filth, that <qex>guzzle</qex> most impure.</q>
<rj><qau>Marston.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guzzler</ent>⟦br⟧
